Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers Asahi, Yomiuri,
Mainichi, Nihon Keizai: -- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi said
Friday that the House of Representatives should not be dissolved to
hold general elections before the Diet (parliament) passes a bill to
streamline the lower house. Mainichi: -- The percentage of university
graduating students in spring who have already scored job offers hit a
record low, a governemnt survey showed Friday. The survey said that
some 241,000 students graduating from Japan's universities, junior
colleges and senior high schools still have not found jobs, Asahi,
Mainichi, Nihon Keizai: -- Nippon Life Insurance Co. has decided to
join an alliance of the Mitsubishi and Sumitomo business groups for the
development and management of a computer system to handle customer data
for a Japanese version of the U.S. 401 (K) pension plan.
